described in the present paper. 
<taxonomicName authority="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev, 2006" authorityName="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2006" box="[559,667,1306,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thaicus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[559,667,1306,1330]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035">P. thaicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[674,766,1306,1330]" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev, 2006" authorityName="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2006" box="[823,955,1306,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siamensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[823,955,1306,1330]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035">P. siamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[962,1053,1306,1330]" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differ from the new species primarily by more slender mid femur (1.5 times broader than fore femur and 2.0 times broader than fore femur, respectively). 
<taxonomicName authority="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev, 2006" authorityName="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2006" box="[748,887,1370,1394]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="isaanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[748,887,1370,1394]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035">P. isaanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[893,984,1370,1394]" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
appears to be the closest ally to the new species. However, it has shorter postpedicel, a wholly brown sternopleuron and different male terminalia. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bezzi)" baseAuthorityName="Bezzi" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[668,914,1435,1459]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candidiseta">
<emphasis box="[668,823,1435,1459]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035">P. candidiseta</emphasis>
(Bezzi)
</taxonomicName>
(known from a female taken in 
<collectingCountry box="[239,326,1467,1491]" name="Taiwan" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
only) differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev, 2006" authorityName="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2006" box="[547,688,1467,1491]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nuadkhao" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[547,688,1467,1491]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035">P. nuadkhao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[696,788,1467,1491]" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by wholly yellow mesonotum and wholly black thoracic pleura (
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi M" box="[478,613,1499,1523]" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035" pagination="442 - 496" refId="ref15141" refString="Bezzi M. 1912. Rhagionidae et Empididae ex insula Formosa a clar. H. Sauter missae. Annales Historico- Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici 10: 442 - 496." type="journal article" year="1912">Bezzi 1912</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="(Brunetti)" baseAuthorityName="Brunetti" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[633,897,1499,1523]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nepalensis">
<emphasis box="[633,772,1499,1523]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035">P. nepalensis</emphasis>
(Brunetti)
</taxonomicName>
(known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1063,1133,1499,1523]" name="Nepal" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035">Nepal</collectingCountry>
also has mesonotum with two small spots) possesses pale yellowish grey pubescence on the occiput, wholly grey thoracic pleura, uniformly pale brownish yellow legs and rather large male terminalia (
<bibRefCitation author="Brunetti E" box="[336,506,1596,1620]" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035" pagination="11 - 45" refId="ref15196" refString="Brunetti E. 1913. New Indian Empididae. Records of the Indian Museum 9: 11 - 45." type="journal article" year="1913">Brunetti 1913</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Brunetti E" box="[520,584,1596,1620]" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035" refId="ref15216" refString="Brunetti E. 1920. Diptera Brachycera, volume I. In: Shipley AE, editor. Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. London: Taylor &amp; Francis 401 p." type="book" year="1920">1920</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Melander" authorityName="Melander" box="[606,919,1596,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinolentus">
<emphasis box="[606,798,1596,1620]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035">P. sanguinolentus</emphasis>
Melander
</taxonomicName>
(known after a female taken from Java only) can be readily distinguished from the new species by the wholly yellow mesonotum and black scutellum (
<bibRefCitation author="de Meijere JCH" box="[618,818,1661,1685]" pageId="6" pageNumber="4035" pagination="1 - 99" refId="ref15320" refString="de Meijere JCH. 1914. Studien uber Sudostasiatische Dipteren. VIII. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie 56: 1 - 99." type="journal article" year="1914">de Meijere 1914</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
